  "prompt": "How did Khal Drogo end up dying from what originally looked like a pretty minor flesh wound?",
  "response": "Khal Drogo, a character from George R.R. Martin's \"A Song of Ice and Fire\" series, and its television adaptation \"Game of Thrones\", sustained a seemingly minor wound during a skirmish. Initially, the injury appeared superficial, but it became seriously infected. Against Drogo\u2019s wishes, Daenerys sought the help of Mirri Maz Duur, a healer and priestess. \n\nRather than healing him, Mirri's treatment worsened Drogo's condition, leading to severe infection and eventually rendering him catatonic. Daenerys then tried to save him through a blood magic ritual performed by Mirri Maz Duur, which demanded a life in exchange. Ultimately, the ritual failed in its intended purpose and Drogo remained in a vegetative state. Daenerys, realizing that he would never recover, chose to end his suffering and smothered him with a pillow. This tragic turn was a result of both the infection from the wound and the subsequent misguided treatment.",
